text: Cito may refer to: * Cito Culver, American professional baseball shortstop in the New York Yankees organization * Cito Gaston, former Major League Baseball outfielder and manager * Claus Cito (1882 – 1965), Luxembourgian sculptor * Mercedes-Benz Cito, a low-floor midibus built by EvoBus for Continental Europe between 1999 and 2003 * Latin for urgent / rapid. CITO may refer to: * CITO- TV, Canadian television station * Cache In Trash Out, abbreviated to CITO, are geocaching events and coordinated activities of trash pickup and other maintenance tasks in to improve the environment.
